## Findings Summary

| # | Issue | OWASP | Severity |
|---|-------|-------|----------|
| 1 | `/users` exposes PII without authentication | A01 Broken Access Control | **High** |
| 2 | No security headers (helmet) | A05 Security Misconfiguration | Medium |
| 3 | `X-Powered-By` header leaks framework | A05 Security Misconfiguration | Low |
| 4 | No rate limiting / DoS protection | A04 Insecure Design | Medium |
| 5 | No CORS policy defined | A05 Security Misconfiguration | Low–Medium |
| 6 | No error-handling middleware | A09 Logging & Monitoring / A05 | Medium |
| 7 | No request logging | A09 Logging & Monitoring | Low |
| 8 | No HTTPS / TLS termination guidance | A02 Cryptographic Failures | Medium (deploy-time) |
| 9 | No request body size limits (if extended) | A04 Insecure Design | Low (preventive) |
| 10 | Unhandled process-level errors | A05 | Low |

### What I explicitly did NOT find
- **No injection** (A03): zero user input reaches any query, template, `eval`, `exec`, or filesystem call.
- **No broken authentication** (A07): there is no authentication to break — but see #1 (it *should* exist on `/users`).
- **No vulnerable deps** (A06): only `express` is imported; run `npm audit` in CI to cover this over time.
- **No SSRF** (A10): no outbound HTTP calls.

---

