```js
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    ...
  ]);
});
```

Emails are PII. Exposing them enables enumeration, spam/phishing targeting, and — if the list later contains real users — GDPR/CCPA issues.

**Fix:** Require authentication and authorization, and return only fields the caller is entitled to see.

```js
const requireAuth = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.replace(/^Bearer\s+/i, '');
  if (!token || !verifyToken(token)) return res.sendStatus(401);
  next();
};

app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  // Only expose emails to admins; otherwise omit.
  const publicView = users.map(u =>
    req.user.role === 'admin' ? u : { id: u.id, name: u.name }
  );
  res.json(publicView);
});
```

