**Issue:** `app.listen(3000, ...)` binds to `0.0.0.0` by default and hardcodes the port. In containerized or shared environments this exposes the service more broadly than intended.

**Recommendation:**

```js
const PORT = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
const HOST = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1';
app.listen(PORT, HOST, () => console.log(`Server running on http://${HOST}:${PORT}`));
```

