The file is only 23 lines and consists of two hardcoded GET endpoints (`/health`, `/users`) with no user input, no database, no authentication logic, and no file/command/template operations. Many OWASP Top 10 categories (A03 Injection, A08 Software/Data Integrity, A10 SSRF) **do not apply** because the code lacks the surface area for them. I won't fabricate findings. Below are the issues that *do* genuinely apply, plus hardening recommendations if this code will be expanded.

