The file as written has **no exploitable vulnerabilities** — it has no attack surface beyond two read-only endpoints returning static data. The real action items are baseline hardening (helmet, rate limit, error handler, disable `x-powered-by`, explicit host binding) and running `npm audit` against the dependency tree, which I can't see from this file alone. If you'd like, share `package.json` and I'll review dependencies.

